The paper deals with multistage combinatorial optimization problems, specifically for matroids and matchings. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a common topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
